{"word":"κατοικτίζω","slug":"κατοικτίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κατοικτίζω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>σω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:κατοικτείρω'><el>κατοικτείρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to bewail oneself, utter lamentations</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; so in aor1 <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>κατῳκτίσθην</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>;—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, as in <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>Causal, <i>to excite pity</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}